      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that makes sense. it sounds pretty risky though. are there any specific parts of that wording that seem particularly \"hidden\" or like they're designed to catch someone off guard? like, is there anything in there that isn't immediately obvious but could end up being a major headache later?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right to be cautious. One part that might seem a bit tricky is the phrase \"including reasonable attorneys' fees.\" This means that the Client can potentially ask you to cover their legal costs if they have to take legal action against you. This can add up quickly, especially if the case drags on. Another potentially tricky part is \"negligent or more culpable act or omission.\" This broad language can be open to interpretation, meaning that even minor mistakes could be considered negligent or more culpable, depending on how things are viewed legally. It's always a good idea to have a lawyer review the contract to fully understand the implications.",
